                        "content": "<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure><img sizes=\"(max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px\" src=\"https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/5D4EE414-2482-413B-A194-7D3EB34D8321-Copy-754x606.jpeg\" width=\"754\" alt=\"Southwest drink coupons. These won't work since they are expired. - Photo: JL Johnson\" srcset=\"https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/5D4EE414-2482-413B-A194-7D3EB34D8321-Copy-754x606.jpeg 754w, https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/5D4EE414-2482-413B-A194-7D3EB34D8321-Copy-250x201.jpeg 250w, https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/5D4EE414-2482-413B-A194-7D3EB34D8321-Copy-768x618.jpeg 768w, https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/5D4EE414-2482-413B-A194-7D3EB34D8321-Copy.jpeg 1093w\" class=\"wp-image-52947\" height=\"606\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Southwest drink coupons. These won’t work since they are expired. – Photo: JL Johnson</figcaption></figure></div>\n<p>Southwest flyers, rejoice! The airline has <strong><span>finally</span></strong> added a non-alcoholic option to their premium beverage menu. This is something I’ve wanted for over a decade. I even included it in my 2019 <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.airlinereporter.com/2019/01/whats-next-for-southwest-airlines-an-elite-flyers-wishlist/\" target=\"_blank\">A-List wish list</a>. </p>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure><img sizes=\"(max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px\" src=\"https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Espresso-1-754x565.jpg\" width=\"754\" alt=\"Community Coffee's new Espresso option. - Photo: JL Johnson\" srcset=\"https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Espresso-1-754x565.jpg 754w, https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Espresso-1-250x187.jpg 250w, https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Espresso-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://www.airlinereporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Espresso-1.jpg 927w\" class=\"wp-image-61202\" height=\"565\"><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Community Coffee’s new Espresso option – Photo: JL Johnson</figcaption></figure></div>\n<p>During the opening day of <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.airlinereporter.com/2023/02/kansas-city-opens-its-new-unified-terminal-tomorrow-we-had-a-sneak-peek-and-it-is-awesome/\" target=\"_blank\">MCI’s new airport terminal</a>, the fine folks at the LUV airline were handing their new Community Coffee Espresso + Cream beverage. It’s good. If you are familiar with the store-bought bottles of Starbucks Frappuccino, it’s a lot like that. Only not nearly as sweet which is a good thing in my book. </p>\n<p>Laura Swift with the Southwest Airlines media team confirmed, “the new Espresso + Cream can be purchased with a valid, non-expired SWA drink coupon.”</p>\n<p>As a non-drinker I’ve made it a habit to routinely give away my drink coupons. But now that there’s a non-alcoholic pick-me-up option I might have to get a little more stingy. So go book a business select fare which includes a free premium drink, or fly 10 revenue segments to earn four coupons of your own <img alt=\"☺\" src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/263a.png\" class=\"wp-smiley\"> </p>",
